{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011PdS8DCSDhWJrgHZKPh19f","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Assuming Node.js + Express (unverified), do scaffold with `npm init -y` and install `express express-session connect-redis redis bcrypt`. Verify Node.js + Express before acting.\n2. Assuming Redis available (unverified), do configure `express-session` with `connect-redis` store, `sess:` prefix, 24h TTL, and a 32-byte secret from env. Verify Redis before acting.\n3. Assuming HTTPS in production (unverified), do set cookie flags `httpOnly: true`, `secure: true`, `sameSite: 'lax'`, `maxAge: 86400000`. Verify HTTPS before acting.\n4. Assuming same-origin frontend (unverified), do skip CSRF tokens and rely on `SameSite=Lax`; otherwise add `csurf`. Verify same-origin frontend before acting.\n5. Implement `POST /login` (bcrypt verify, set `req.session.userId`), `POST /logout` (`req.session.destroy`), `GET /me` (guard middleware checking `req.session.userId`)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3119d2311555e463 (use SendMessage with to: 'a3119d2311555e463' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 17912\ntool_uses: 0\nduration_ms: 7810</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a7c408ec-e92a-45de-8a71-91ed131b0b69","uuid":"3bdbf949-1312-49f2-a85d-b037bfa26288","timestamp":"2026-05-01T07:13:35.113Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"## Task\n> Add auth to this API. The frontend uses cookies.\n\n## Orientation Findings\n1. The working directory contains no API source files. The only non-git files are `D-output.txt` (a prior plan summary) and `E-output.jsonl` (a session log). This is a blank repository with a single \"seed\" commit.\n2. No `package.json`, `requirements.txt`, `Cargo.toml`, or any language manifest is present -- the framework, runtime, and language are unknown.\n3. No existing routes, middleware, models, or configuration files exist.\n4. The only constraint provided: the fronte