{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01X28aBwsBFmtVtiDQHeZHyW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"--- Strategic Direction ---\n\n1. Assuming Node.js + Express (unverified), do scaffold with `npm init -y` and install `express express-session connect-redis redis bcrypt`. Verify Node.js + Express before acting.\n2. Assuming Redis available (unverified), do configure `express-session` with `connect-redis` store, `sess:` prefix, 24h TTL, and a 32-byte secret from env. Verify Redis before acting.\n3. Assuming HTTPS in production (unverified), do set cookie flags `httpOnly: true`, `secure: true`, `sameSite: 'lax'`, `maxAge: 86400000`. Verify HTTPS before acting.\n4. Assuming same-origin frontend (unverified), do skip CSRF tokens and rely on `SameSite=Lax`; otherwise add `csurf`. Verify same-origin frontend before acting.\n5. Implement `POST /login` (bcrypt verify, set `req.session.userId`), `POST /logout` (`req.session.destroy`), `GET /me` (guard middleware checking `req.session.userId`).\n\n--- End Strategic Direction ---"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1075,"cache_read_input_tokens":62222,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1075},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a7c408ec-e92a-45de-8a71-91ed131b0b69","uuid":"3b3c779a-1c6f-4d70-95ba-aeb96db97094"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01X28aBwsBFmtVtiDQHeZHyW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PfV9iNaZBbVdfErbmRuaom","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\LarsGyrupBrinkNielse\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\lz-advisor-def-QSgX\\plans\\add-cookie-auth.plan.md","content":"# Plan: Add Cookie-Based Auth to API\n\n## Strategic Direction\n\n1. Assuming Node.js + Express (unverified), do scaffold with `npm init -y` and install `express express-session connect-redis redis bcrypt`. Verify Node.js + Express before acting.\n2. Assuming Redis available (unverified), do configure `express-session` with `connect-redis` store, `sess:` prefix, 24h TTL, and a 32-byte secret from env. Verify Redis before acting.\n3. Assuming HTTPS in production (unverified), do set cookie flags `httpOnly: true`, `secure: true`, `sameSite: 'lax'`, `maxAge: 86400000`. Verify HTTPS before acting.\n4. Assuming same-origin frontend (unverified), do skip CSRF tokens and rely on `SameSite=Lax`; otherwise add `csurf`. Verify same-origin frontend before acting.\n5. Implement `POST /login` (bcrypt verify, set `req.session.userId`), `POST /logout` (`req.session.destroy`), `GET /me` (guard middleware checking `req.session.userId`).\n\n## Steps\n\n1. **Verify runtime and scaffold**\n   - File: `package.json`\n   - Change: Run `npm init -y` to create `package.json`; install `express`, `express-session`, `connect-redis`, `redis`, `bcrypt`, `dotenv` as production deps, and `@types/*` / TypeScript tooling as dev deps if TypeScript is preferred.\n   - Rationale: Advisor step 1 -- confirm Node.js/Express before acting. If the runtime differs (Fastify, Hono, Koa), adapt session middleware accordingly; the cookie-flag and route shape remain the same.\n\n2. **Configure environment**\n   - File: `.env` (gitignored), `.env.example`\n   - Change: Add `SESSION_SECRET` (32-byte random hex), `REDIS_URL` (defaults to `redis://localhost:6379`), `NODE_ENV`.\n   - Rationale: Advisor step 2 requires a 32-byte secret from env; never hardcode the secret.\n\n3. **Set up session middleware**\n   - File: `src/middleware/session.ts` (or `session.js`)\n   - Change: Export an `express-session` instance configured with `connect-redis` store (`sess:` prefix, 24h TTL), cookie flags `httpOnly: true`, `secure: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production'`, `sameSite: 'lax'`, `maxAge: 86400000`.\n   - Rationale: Advisor steps 2-3 -- Redis store avoids in-memory session loss on restart; `secure` flag gated on `NODE_ENV` so local dev works over HTTP.\n\n4. **Add auth guard middleware**\n   - File: `src/middleware/requireAuth.ts`\n   - Change: Export a middleware that checks `req.session.userId`; if absent, respond 401. Mount on all protected routes.\n   - Rationale: Advisor step 5 -- the guard is the reusable enforcement point for session authentication.\n\n5. **Implement auth routes**\n   - File: `src/routes/auth.ts`\n   - Change: Define `POST /login` (look up user by email/username, `bcrypt.compare` password hash, on success set `req.session.userId` and return 200), `POST /logout` (`req.session.destroy`, clear cookie, return 204), `GET /me` (protected by `requireAuth`, return session user data).\n   - Rationale: Advisor step 5 -- these three endpoints are the minimal auth surface for a cookie-session API.\n\n6. **Wire up in the app entry point**\n   - File: `src/app.ts` (or `index.js`)\n   - Change: Import and register session middleware before routes; mount auth router at `/auth`; apply `requireAuth` to any existing protected routes.\n   - Rationale: Session middleware must execute before any route handler reads `req.session`.\n\n7. **Add CSRF protection if cross-origin**\n   - File: `src/middleware/csrf.ts` (conditional)\n   - Change: If the frontend is served from a different origin than the API, install `csurf` (or `csrf-csrf` for ESM), generate a token on `GET /auth/csrf-token`, and validate on state-changing requests.\n   - Rationale: Advisor step 4 -- `SameSite=Lax` is sufficient for same-origin; cross-origin SPAs need an explicit CSRF token because `Lax` does not protect cross-origin POST.\n\n## Key Decisions\n\n- **Session store -- Redis vs. in-memory**: The advisor assumes Redis is available. In-memory store (`express-session` default) is acceptable for development but loses sessions on restart and does not scale horizontally. Verify Redis availability; if unavailable, start with in-memory and note the limitation.\n- **bcrypt for password hashing**: Correct default. Do not use MD5, SHA1, or unsalted hashes. `bcrypt.compare` is constant-time, preventing timing attacks.\n- **`secure: true` in production**: Cookies without `Secure` are transmitted over HTTP, exposing session IDs. Gate on `NODE_ENV` so local dev does not require HTTPS.\n- **CSRF risk**: `SameSite=Lax` blocks cross-site POST initiated by third-party pages but does NOT protect cross-origin SPA requests made with `fetch`. Confirm whether the frontend is same-origin before omitting `csurf`.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nSteps 1 and 2 must complete before steps 3-7 (packages and env must exist first). Steps 3 and 4 are independent of each other and can be done in parallel. Step 5 depends on step 4 (uses `requireAuth`). Step 6 depends on steps 3, 4, and 5. Step 7 is conditional and can be done in parallel with step 6 if CSRF is needed.\n\n## Verdict\n\n**Verdict scope:** scope: api-correctness\n\nThe plan covers correctness of the proposed Node.js/Express session-cookie authentication integration. It does NOT cover security threats beyond the advisor's CSRF and cookie-flag guidance (use `/lz-advisor.security-review` after implementation), performance, or accessibility. Downstream skills reading this plan MUST check scope-match per `references/context-packaging.md` \"Scope-Disambiguated Provenance Markers\" before treating the verdict as authoritative for their question.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1075,"cache_read_input_tokens":62222,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1075},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a7c408ec-e92a-45de-8a71-91ed131b0b69","uuid":"1012ddc3-be00-4e65-accc-28b4c54cbb2e"}
